WEBVTT

03:42.223 --> 03:48.438
<i>Guenevere, Guenevere</i>

03:48.605 --> 03:54.611
<i>In that dim, mournful year</i>

03:54.777 --> 04:01.034
<i>Saw the men she held so dear</i>

04:01.200 --> 04:08.041
<i>Go to war for Guenevere</i>

04:21.095 --> 04:24.390
The rules of battle are not for
Lancelot Du Lac, Your Majesty.

04:24.599 --> 04:26.476
Let us attack now while they sleep.

04:28.770 --> 04:33.191
We will attack when
I give the command, at dawn.

04:45.870 --> 04:47.205
Merlyn...

04:48.790 --> 04:51.250
...why is Jenny in that castle...

04:51.459 --> 04:54.671
...behind walls I cannot enter?

04:55.964 --> 04:59.175
How did I blunder into this...

04:59.801 --> 05:02.387
...agonizing absurdity?

05:06.975 --> 05:10.895
When did I stumble?
Where did I go wrong?

05:13.898 --> 05:16.734
Should I not have loved her?

05:18.987 --> 05:22.240
Then I should not have been...

05:22.699 --> 05:24.075
...born.

05:24.617 --> 05:25.994
Oh, Merlyn...

05:27.161 --> 05:29.414
...how did it happen?

05:29.998 --> 05:32.000
I haven't got much time.

05:34.168 --> 05:36.587
A thin inch of sunlight...

05:36.754 --> 05:39.549
...the arrows begin to fly.

05:42.510 --> 05:43.845
Merlyn...

05:44.345 --> 05:48.099
...if I am to die...

05:48.307 --> 05:49.726
...in battle...

05:52.520 --> 05:55.857
...please do not let me die...

05:56.065 --> 05:57.692
...bewildered.

06:01.362 --> 06:02.947
<i>Think, Arthur.</i>

06:03.156 --> 06:04.949
<i>Think back.</i>

06:22.717 --> 06:24.135
Think back.

06:24.302 --> 06:25.887
Think back!

06:26.888 --> 06:28.765
Oh, Merlyn!

06:31.059 --> 06:32.643
Think back.

06:32.810 --> 06:34.771
Think back!

06:36.898 --> 06:38.316
Think...

06:38.483 --> 06:39.984
...back.

06:40.902 --> 06:45.531
Back! To one of the most
important days of your life.

06:47.033 --> 06:48.785
Oh, yes, heh!

06:56.250 --> 06:57.376
Hello.

07:04.258 --> 07:06.094
My name is Arthur.

07:06.427 --> 07:08.721
I think I'll call you...

07:09.347 --> 07:10.389
...Wart.

07:11.265 --> 07:13.476
"I think I'll call you Wart."

07:15.269 --> 07:16.813
No, no, no!

07:17.021 --> 07:19.357
Now you've gone too far back.

07:19.649 --> 07:22.360
Shoo, shoo, shoo!

07:23.402 --> 07:25.571
Not the day you met me!

07:26.114 --> 07:29.367
The day you met Guenevere.

07:30.952 --> 07:33.121
The day she came...

07:33.454 --> 07:35.039
...to Camelot.

07:37.125 --> 07:39.377
That's the beginning.

07:45.049 --> 07:46.551
Yes.

08:21.711 --> 08:23.296
I know...

08:23.546 --> 08:25.131
...what my people...

08:25.339 --> 08:27.425
...are thinking tonight.

08:27.842 --> 08:29.552
<i>I know what my people</i>

08:29.719 --> 08:31.429
<i>Are thinking tonight</i>

08:32.013 --> 08:35.765
<i>As home through the shadows
They wander</i>

08:36.851 --> 08:41.022
<i>Everyone smiling in secret delight</i>

08:41.522 --> 08:44.692
<i>As they stare at the castle and ponder</i>

08:46.360 --> 08:49.864
<i>Whenever the wind blows this way</i>

08:50.698 --> 08:54.660
<i>You can almost hear everyone say...</i>

08:57.205 --> 09:00.708
<i>...I wonder what the king
Is doing tonight</i>

09:00.917 --> 09:04.045
<i>What merriment is the king
Pursuing tonight?</i>

09:04.378 --> 09:07.548
<i>The candles at the court
They never burned as bright</i>

09:07.882 --> 09:10.885
<i>I wonder what the king
Is up to tonight</i>

09:11.219 --> 09:14.889
<i>How goes the final hour
As he sees the bridal bower</i>

09:15.223 --> 09:17.558
<i>Being legally and regally prepared?</i>

09:18.392 --> 09:21.896
<i>Well, I'll tell you what the king
Is doing tonight</i>

09:22.104 --> 09:25.233
<i>He's scared Oh, he's scared</i>

09:27.735 --> 09:31.656
<i>You mean that a king who fought a dragon
Whacked him in two and fixed his wagon</i>

09:31.822 --> 09:34.742
<i>Goes to wed in terror and distress?</i>

09:34.992 --> 09:36.452
<i>Oh, yes!</i>

09:36.744 --> 09:40.414
<i>A warrior who's so calm in battle
Even his armor doesn't rattle</i>

09:40.748 --> 09:42.917
<i>Faces a woman petrified with fright?</i>

09:44.043 --> 09:45.086
<i>Right!</i>

09:45.753 --> 09:49.090
<i>You mean the appalling clamoring
That sounds like a blacksmith hammering</i>

09:49.423 --> 09:52.718
<i>Is merely the banging
Of his royal knees?</i>

09:52.969 --> 09:54.512
<i>Please!</i>

09:54.929 --> 09:58.432
<i>You wonder what the king
Is wishing tonight?</i>

09:58.766 --> 10:01.936
<i>He's wishing he were
In Scotland fishing tonight</i>

10:02.270 --> 10:05.773
<i>What occupies his time
While waiting for his bride?</i>

10:06.107 --> 10:09.360
<i>He's searching high and low
For someplace to hide</i>

10:09.777 --> 10:12.613
<i>And, oh, the expectation
The sublime anticipation</i>

10:12.947 --> 10:15.783
<i>He must feel about
The wedding night to come</i>

10:16.784 --> 10:20.454
<i>Well, I'll tell you what the king
Is feeling tonight</i>

10:20.788 --> 10:24.458
<i>He's numb! He shakes!
He quails! He quakes!</i>

10:24.792 --> 10:27.795
<i>And that's what the king is doing</i>

10:34.343 --> 10:35.720
<i>Tonight!</i>

11:03.456 --> 11:05.583
How long before we get to Camelot?

11:05.791 --> 11:09.503
Soon, ma'am, but don't look out there,
it's a ghastly forest.

11:10.129 --> 11:12.965
It's the most ferocious, savage...

11:13.632 --> 11:16.260
...terrifying forest I've ever seen.

11:17.136 --> 11:19.597
I simply adore it.

11:19.764 --> 11:24.143
Does Your Ladyship not realize
that this forest is crawling...

11:24.477 --> 11:26.479
...with outlaws and brigands?

11:26.645 --> 11:29.357
Oh, Clary! You think there's
a chance of meeting one?

11:30.316 --> 11:31.609
Don't say it, ma'am.

11:32.526 --> 11:34.820
It would be marvelous.

11:36.614 --> 11:41.285
Imagine, ma'am, soon you will
not only meet the man you will marry...

11:41.494 --> 11:44.789
...but His Majesty,
King Arthur of England.

11:44.997 --> 11:48.501
And one is the other.
What have you to say to that?

11:49.418 --> 11:51.504
Oh, Clary.

11:51.670 --> 11:55.716
Was there ever a more
inconvenient marriage of convenience?

11:56.509 --> 12:00.471
I am at the golden age of seductability,
and is my fate sealed with a kiss?

12:00.763 --> 12:03.140
Is it?
No, sealed with a seal!

12:08.687 --> 12:11.023
<i>Where are all the simple joys</i>

12:11.190 --> 12:12.858
<i>Of maidenhood?</i>

12:13.692 --> 12:18.197
<i>Where are all those
Adoring, daring boys?</i>

12:19.365 --> 12:22.535
<i>Where's the knight pining so for me?</i>

12:22.868 --> 12:26.038
<i>He leaps to death in woe for me</i>

12:26.539 --> 12:30.835
<i>Oh where are a maiden's simple joys?</i>

12:32.711 --> 12:37.049
<i>Shan't I have the normal life
A maiden should?</i>

12:38.008 --> 12:42.388
<i>Shall I never be rescued in the wood?</i>

12:43.722 --> 12:47.059
<i>Shall two knights never tilt for me</i>

12:47.393 --> 12:50.563
<i>And let their blood be spilt for me?</i>

12:51.230 --> 12:53.899
<i>Oh, where are the simple joys</i>

12:54.233 --> 12:56.902
<i>Of maidenhood?</i>

12:58.070 --> 13:01.240
<i>Shall I never be disputed for</i>

13:01.907 --> 13:04.577
<i>Or on any minstrel's lips?</i>

13:05.578 --> 13:09.457
<i>Never have my face recruited for</i>

13:09.915 --> 13:14.211
<i>Launching countless ships?</i>

13:16.255 --> 13:20.593
<i>Where are the simple joys
Of maidenhood?</i>

13:21.427 --> 13:25.764
<i>Are those sweet, gentle pleasures
Gone for good?</i>

13:27.266 --> 13:30.227
<i>Shall a feud not begin for me?</i>

13:30.394 --> 13:33.939
<i>Shall kith not kill their kin for me?</i>

13:34.607 --> 13:38.444
<i>Oh where are the trivial joys?</i>

13:39.445 --> 13:43.282
<i>Harmless, convivial joys?</i>

13:44.116 --> 13:46.952
<i>Where are the simple joys</i>

13:47.286 --> 13:50.372
<i>Of maidenhood?</i>

13:50.915 --> 13:51.957
Halt!

13:52.291 --> 13:55.794
Her Highness will rest here
while the Royal Hairdresser...

13:56.086 --> 13:57.421
...attends her.

13:57.630 --> 14:00.174
Can someone help with this canopy?

14:00.341 --> 14:02.927
Take that case down
and bring it over here.

14:03.093 --> 14:04.762
Hurry up now, would you, please?

14:04.929 --> 14:06.639
Careful now.

14:07.014 --> 14:08.891
Clarinda.

14:11.477 --> 14:14.563
I should like some tea
while I'm being coifed.

14:14.730 --> 14:16.774
Yes, Your Highness.

14:16.941 --> 14:18.817
Can he get somebody to help there?

14:18.984 --> 14:22.196
You, you come over here and help me.

14:24.949 --> 14:28.160
Bring that horse over here.
He needs water.

14:56.897 --> 14:58.857
St. Genevieve.

15:00.651 --> 15:03.028
<i>St. Genevieve</i>

15:04.363 --> 15:06.365
<i>It's Guenevere</i>

15:08.033 --> 15:09.368
Remember me?

15:10.786 --> 15:12.580
<i>St. Genevieve</i>

15:13.247 --> 15:15.332
<i>St. Genevieve</i>

15:16.375 --> 15:19.003
I'm over here, beneath this tree!

15:20.254 --> 15:23.382
<i>You know how faithful and devout I am</i>

15:24.383 --> 15:27.595
<i>You must admit
I've always been a lamb</i>

15:29.722 --> 15:33.058
<i>But Genevieve, St. Genevieve</i>

15:35.060 --> 15:38.355
<i>I won't obey you anymore
You've gone a bit too far</i>

15:38.564 --> 15:41.817
<i>I won't be bid and bargained for
Like beads at a bazaar</i>

15:42.192 --> 15:44.945
<i>St. Genevieve, I've run away
Eluded them and fled</i>

15:45.904 --> 15:50.034
<i>And from now on I intend
To pray to someone else instead</i>

15:56.081 --> 15:59.752
<i>Oh, Genevieve, St. Genevieve</i>

16:01.587 --> 16:05.090
<i>Where were you
When my youth was sold?</i>

16:07.426 --> 16:09.595
<i>Dear Genevieve</i>

16:10.596 --> 16:12.806
<i>Sweet Genevieve</i>

16:13.766 --> 16:19.647
<i>Shan't I be young before I'm old?</i>

16:23.609 --> 16:25.319
A thousand pardons, my lady.

16:25.527 --> 16:27.154
Don't run, I won't harm you.

16:27.363 --> 16:29.948
You lie! You'll leap on me
and throw me down!

16:30.449 --> 16:31.825
I'll do no such thing.

16:32.034 --> 16:34.286
You'll carry me off on your shoulder!

16:34.495 --> 16:37.581
No, I swear by the sword Excalibur
I won't touch you.

16:38.916 --> 16:39.958
Why not?

16:40.292 --> 16:44.129
How dare you insult me in this fashion?
Do my looks repel you?

16:44.630 --> 16:48.217
- No, you're beautiful!
- Did you hear me praying?

16:48.425 --> 16:50.636
I couldn't help it.
You did pray loudly.

16:50.844 --> 16:52.429
So you know who I am?

16:52.638 --> 16:54.473
Yes, you're Guenevere.

16:54.682 --> 16:58.936
So that accounts for your polite,
respectful, despicable behavior?

16:59.103 --> 17:00.312
Oh.

17:00.479 --> 17:02.981
Why isn't Merlyn here?

17:03.190 --> 17:05.483
- Who?
- Merlyn. He's my teacher.

17:05.983 --> 17:09.988
He's the wisest man alive. He'd know
what to do. He lives backwards.

17:10.781 --> 17:14.451
- Beg your pardon?
- He lives backwards.

17:14.992 --> 17:17.496
He doesn't age.
He...

17:17.704 --> 17:18.914
...youthens?

17:21.500 --> 17:24.169
He can remember the future...

17:24.377 --> 17:26.672
...so he can tell you
what you'll do in it.

17:31.301 --> 17:32.386
Come here.

17:34.096 --> 17:35.139
Please.

17:38.016 --> 17:39.518
Close your eyes.

17:41.687 --> 17:42.813
Please.

17:44.022 --> 17:46.316
Now just turn, gently.

17:47.484 --> 17:48.527
Now....

17:48.694 --> 17:51.196
Very slowly, open them.

17:53.866 --> 17:56.410
Do you see that castle?

17:58.412 --> 17:59.455
Yeah.

17:59.621 --> 18:03.375
It used to light up
in a sort of pink glow.

18:05.836 --> 18:08.714
When I was young,
everything looked a little pink to me.

18:10.215 --> 18:12.134
But then, one....

18:13.177 --> 18:16.096
When Merlyn left,
he took all the pink with him.

18:19.224 --> 18:21.268
Don't stare. It's rude.

18:22.561 --> 18:23.979
Who are you?

18:26.732 --> 18:27.775
Well....

18:27.941 --> 18:30.527
Actually, they call me Wart, actually.

18:32.738 --> 18:37.034
- You sure you heard them properly?
- It's a nickname. Merlyn gave it to me.

18:40.871 --> 18:42.247
Wart, what--?

18:42.414 --> 18:44.041
- Is it really Wart?
- Mm-hm.

18:45.876 --> 18:47.085
Wart.

18:47.252 --> 18:49.713
Why don't you run away with me?

18:50.005 --> 18:51.048
I?

18:51.215 --> 18:54.593
You could be my protector,
defend me all over the world...

18:54.927 --> 18:56.887
...in France, in England,
Mongolia, Scotland.

18:57.054 --> 18:59.556
Oh, what a wonderful dream you spin.

18:59.723 --> 19:02.726
And how easy it would be for me
to be caught up in it.

19:03.268 --> 19:04.436
But...

19:05.229 --> 19:06.730
...I must decline.

19:07.231 --> 19:08.690
You forcing me to stay?

19:08.982 --> 19:10.275
Oh, no, my lady!

19:10.484 --> 19:14.321
If you persist in escaping, I'll find
somebody brave to accompany you.

19:14.947 --> 19:17.658
Then do so at once before
your wretched king finds me.

19:18.450 --> 19:20.786
Oh, do look around you, my lady!

19:21.620 --> 19:22.996
Reconsider.

19:23.789 --> 19:26.124
Camelot is unique.

19:26.750 --> 19:31.296
And we have, by far and away,
the most equable climate in all England.

19:32.631 --> 19:34.675
Ordained by decree.

19:37.719 --> 19:39.179
Oh, come now!

19:41.807 --> 19:43.100
It's true.

19:44.059 --> 19:46.019
Heh, it's true!

19:46.812 --> 19:49.439
<i>The Crown has made it clear</i>

19:49.648 --> 19:52.359
<i>The climate must be perfect</i>

19:52.568 --> 19:54.778
<i>All the year</i>

19:55.487 --> 19:59.324
<i>A law was made
A distant moon ago here</i>

20:00.158 --> 20:03.495
<i>July and August cannot be too hot</i>

20:04.830 --> 20:08.500
<i>And there's a legal limit
To the snow here</i>

20:09.501 --> 20:11.003
<i>In Camelot</i>

20:14.339 --> 20:17.801
<i>The winter is forbidden till December</i>

20:18.677 --> 20:22.806
<i>And exits March the second on the dot</i>

20:23.181 --> 20:27.185
<i>By order, summer lingers
Through September</i>

20:28.020 --> 20:29.187
<i>In Camelot</i>

20:32.816 --> 20:33.984
<i>Camelot</i>

20:34.943 --> 20:36.028
<i>Camelot</i>

20:37.195 --> 20:39.573
<i>I know it sounds a bit bizarre</i>

20:41.366 --> 20:43.201
<i>But in Camelot</i>

20:44.620 --> 20:45.954
<i>Camelot</i>

20:46.538 --> 20:49.333
<i>That's how conditions are</i>

20:51.209 --> 20:55.213
<i>The rain may never fall
Till after sundown</i>

20:56.048 --> 20:59.384
<i>By 8 the morning fog must disappear</i>

21:00.552 --> 21:05.223
<i>In short, there's simply not
A more congenial spot</i>

21:05.724 --> 21:08.894
<i>For happily-ever-aftering</i>

21:09.227 --> 21:14.900
<i>Than here in Camelot</i>

21:17.402 --> 21:20.864
And I suppose the autumn leaves
fall into neat little piles?

21:21.740 --> 21:25.535
Oh, no, my lady.
They, pfft, blow away completely.

21:26.244 --> 21:28.413
At night, of course.

21:33.460 --> 21:35.379
Of course.

21:36.838 --> 21:38.215
<i>Camelot</i>

21:39.049 --> 21:40.092
<i>Camelot</i>

21:40.258 --> 21:42.928
<i>I know it gives a person pause</i>

21:45.263 --> 21:47.057
<i>But in Camelot</i>

21:48.225 --> 21:49.601
<i>Camelot</i>

21:50.102 --> 21:52.437
<i>Those are the legal laws</i>

21:55.607 --> 21:59.111
<i>The snow may never
Slush upon the hillside</i>

22:00.779 --> 22:04.616
<i>By 9 p.m.
The moonlight must appear</i>

22:06.284 --> 22:08.620
<i>In short, there's simply not</i>

22:09.538 --> 22:11.623
<i>A more congenial spot</i>

22:12.457 --> 22:16.461
<i>For happily-ever-aftering</i>

22:17.963 --> 22:20.465
<i>Than here</i>

22:20.799 --> 22:23.635
<i>In Camelot</i>

22:28.390 --> 22:31.059
Look! There, on the hill!

22:31.727 --> 22:32.811
What?

22:35.564 --> 22:37.274
I'm truly sorry, but...

22:37.441 --> 22:41.028
...I'm-- I'm afraid, on account of me...

22:41.236 --> 22:43.113
- ...you may be hanged!
- Hanged?

22:43.280 --> 22:45.115
Or burnt at the stake for abducting me!

22:45.282 --> 22:48.535
That uncivilized king of yours will....
Defend yourself!

22:50.954 --> 22:54.041
There she is!
But who's that peasant with her?

22:55.125 --> 22:57.085
You rogue.

22:58.545 --> 22:59.963
The king!

23:00.839 --> 23:02.924
- The king!
- His Majesty.

23:03.091 --> 23:06.261
It's the king!

23:06.428 --> 23:08.138
It's the king! Wart, it's the king!

23:08.346 --> 23:10.223
Your Majesty, forgive.... Forgive me.

23:10.557 --> 23:12.309
I did not know it was you.

23:21.651 --> 23:22.986
The king.

23:49.554 --> 23:52.182
When I was a young lad
of 18 years of age...

23:52.390 --> 23:57.145
...our good king, Pendragon, died,
leaving no one to succeed him...

23:57.395 --> 24:01.191
...but a sword stuck through an anvil
that stood on a stone.

24:01.399 --> 24:03.527
Written on it,
in gold letters, it said:

24:03.735 --> 24:06.404
"Who so pulleth this sword
from this stone...

24:06.613 --> 24:08.990
...is rightwise born
King of all England."

24:09.574 --> 24:13.203
Well, many chaps tried to
dislodge it, but they failed.

24:13.411 --> 24:17.415
So finally, a great tournament was
proclaimed for New Year's Day.

24:18.083 --> 24:21.711
All the mightiest knights in England
were assembled at one time to have...

24:21.878 --> 24:23.588
...a go at the sword.

24:27.259 --> 24:28.718
Well....

24:29.553 --> 24:34.099
I-- I-- I went to London as squire
to my cousin, Sir Kay.

24:34.432 --> 24:37.894
On tournament day, Sir Kay found
he had left his sword at home...

24:38.103 --> 24:40.564
...and he gave me
a shilling to fetch it.

24:40.772 --> 24:44.401
Going through London,
I passed a square and saw a sword...

24:44.943 --> 24:47.070
...rising out of a stone.

24:47.279 --> 24:49.072
Not thinking very clearly, I...

24:50.323 --> 24:53.076
...I thought it was a war memorial.

24:57.122 --> 24:59.457
So I decided to borrow it...

24:59.666 --> 25:02.210
...and to save myself the trip.

25:02.627 --> 25:03.920
So I...

25:04.921 --> 25:06.590
...took the sword....

25:07.632 --> 25:09.551
Took the sword and...

25:09.968 --> 25:11.303
...I failed.

25:11.553 --> 25:13.263
So I tried again.

25:14.639 --> 25:16.641
And I failed again.

25:18.810 --> 25:22.314
So, with all my might,
I closed my eyes...

25:23.148 --> 25:24.649
...and I tried...

25:24.858 --> 25:28.445
...one last time.

25:29.654 --> 25:31.031
And, lo!

25:31.239 --> 25:33.491
The sword moved in my hand.

25:36.161 --> 25:37.704
And slowly...

25:38.538 --> 25:42.000
...it slid out of the stone.

25:44.336 --> 25:46.004
I heard...

25:46.213 --> 25:47.464
...a great roar.

25:47.672 --> 25:50.967
I opened my eyes.
The square was full of people saying:

25:51.134 --> 25:53.845
"Long live the king!
Long live...

25:56.723 --> 25:58.016
...the king."

26:04.522 --> 26:06.358
That's how I became king.

26:06.566 --> 26:09.444
I never knew I would be.
I never wanted to be.

26:09.694 --> 26:13.156
And since I am,
I've been ill at ease in my crown.

26:13.531 --> 26:16.534
Until I dropped from the tree...

26:18.203 --> 26:20.121
...and my eyes...

26:20.330 --> 26:22.040
...beheld you.

26:25.710 --> 26:29.965
And then, for the first time...

26:30.173 --> 26:33.718
...I felt like a king.
I was glad to be king.

26:34.719 --> 26:39.307
And most astonishing of all,
I wanted to be the most heroic...

26:39.724 --> 26:42.185
...the wisest, the most...

26:42.602 --> 26:45.063
...splendid king ever to sit...

26:45.272 --> 26:47.357
...on any throne.

27:01.037 --> 27:02.622
Well, if you'll....

27:03.415 --> 27:05.875
If my lady will follow me, I'll...

27:06.042 --> 27:08.712
...I'll find a proper companion...

27:10.505 --> 27:12.382
...to accompany you.

27:35.280 --> 27:38.283
<i>I hear it never rains</i>

27:38.950 --> 27:41.411
<i>Till after sundown</i>

27:43.955 --> 27:49.919
<i>By 8 the morning fog
Must disappear</i>

27:50.962 --> 27:53.631
<i>In short, there's simply not</i>

27:54.632 --> 27:56.968
<i>A more congenial spot</i>

27:57.635 --> 28:01.306
<i>For happily-ever-aftering</i>

28:05.143 --> 28:09.147
<i>Than here</i>

28:09.314 --> 28:16.237
<i>In Camelot</i>

28:33.171 --> 28:38.134
<i>A law was made a distant moon ago here</i>

28:39.386 --> 28:43.223
<i>July and August cannot be too hot</i>

28:45.100 --> 28:50.688
<i>And there's a legal limit
To the snow here</i>

28:51.064 --> 28:52.982
<i>In Camelot</i>

28:54.150 --> 28:56.236
<i>In Camelot</i>

28:57.445 --> 28:58.488
<i>Camelot</i>

29:00.490 --> 29:01.825
<i>Camelot</i>

29:02.325 --> 29:06.079
<i>I know it gives a person pause</i>

29:08.748 --> 29:10.708
<i>But in Camelot</i>

29:12.460 --> 29:14.170
<i>Camelot</i>

29:15.088 --> 29:18.550
<i>Those are the legal laws</i>

29:21.094 --> 29:25.807
<i>The rain may never fall
Till after sundown</i>

29:25.974 --> 29:27.183
<i>In Camelot</i>

29:27.350 --> 29:31.688
<i>By 9 p.m.
The moonlight must appear</i>

29:31.855 --> 29:33.106
<i>In Camelot</i>

29:33.273 --> 29:35.942
<i>In short there's simply not</i>

29:36.109 --> 29:39.154
<i>A more congenial spot</i>

29:39.320 --> 29:44.075
<i>For happily-ever-aftering</i>

29:44.242 --> 29:46.369
<i>Than here</i>

29:46.536 --> 29:53.460
<i>In Camelot</i>

29:57.797 --> 30:00.049
<i>The map of England.</i>

30:00.216 --> 30:01.718
Map, indeed.

30:01.885 --> 30:05.221
A fishnet of ill-begotten kingdoms
ruled by immoral lords...

30:05.555 --> 30:10.393
...battling with their own unlawful
armies over illegal border lines.

30:10.727 --> 30:12.187
And who is...

30:12.395 --> 30:14.230
...king of this...

30:14.439 --> 30:15.773
...jungle?

30:15.940 --> 30:17.066
Hmm?

30:17.233 --> 30:19.903
The man who four years ago
pledged he would become...

30:20.069 --> 30:22.572
...the greatest king
who ever sat on any throne.

30:22.739 --> 30:23.823
I...

30:24.407 --> 30:26.242
...Arthur of England.

30:26.951 --> 30:28.036
Yes.

30:28.244 --> 30:31.414
The greatest warrior in the land.

30:31.748 --> 30:33.833
For what purpose?

30:35.043 --> 30:36.085
Might...

30:36.252 --> 30:39.130
...doesn't always mean right.

30:39.797 --> 30:43.676
What are you saying? To be right
and lose couldn't possibly be right.

30:44.052 --> 30:45.220
Merlyn...

30:46.054 --> 30:48.348
...used to frown on battles.

30:48.556 --> 30:50.475
Yet he always...

30:50.683 --> 30:52.018
...helped me win them.

30:52.227 --> 30:53.269
Why?

30:59.317 --> 31:00.527
Proposition:

31:01.986 --> 31:05.657
Is it far better to be alive than dead?

31:05.949 --> 31:07.283
Yes, far better. Mm.

31:07.784 --> 31:09.452
If that is so...

31:10.161 --> 31:13.081
...then why do we have wars...

31:13.289 --> 31:16.042
...in which people can get killed?

31:16.251 --> 31:17.961
I don't know, do you?

31:18.169 --> 31:19.420
Yes.

31:19.796 --> 31:22.674
Because somebody attacks.

31:23.049 --> 31:24.509
Why do they attack?

31:31.808 --> 31:33.309
Jenny.

31:34.644 --> 31:36.312
Did I ever tell you...

31:36.521 --> 31:39.816
...how Merlyn taught me how to think?

31:40.233 --> 31:41.276
No.

31:41.484 --> 31:44.862
By changing me into animals.

31:45.363 --> 31:47.532
Oh, really! Arthur!

31:51.703 --> 31:54.539
Jenny, I mean by making me believe...

31:55.540 --> 31:57.875
...he had changed me into animals.

31:58.626 --> 32:02.338
For instance, when a hawk
is up there looking down at the world...

32:02.547 --> 32:05.633
...there are no boundaries.

32:06.551 --> 32:07.885
Right?

32:08.511 --> 32:09.804
Hmm.

32:11.306 --> 32:12.515
Yet boundaries are what...

32:12.682 --> 32:14.267
...somebody always attacks about.

32:14.475 --> 32:18.521
And you win by pushing them
back across something that...

32:19.272 --> 32:21.232
...that doesn't exist.

32:21.441 --> 32:25.445
So we have battles for no reason at all.
Why, Jenny, why?

32:25.653 --> 32:28.573
Because ladies love knights.
To see your knight in armor....

32:28.781 --> 32:30.241
That's it, Jenny.

32:30.450 --> 32:32.660
Jenny, that is it!

32:32.869 --> 32:34.120
It's the armor!

32:34.329 --> 32:36.998
It's the armor, Jenny.
The armor.

32:38.207 --> 32:42.378
Look, only the knights are rich enough
to have armor. The foot soldiers....

32:42.545 --> 32:43.921
Well, they have nothing.

32:44.505 --> 32:47.383
So, all that can happen
to a knight is, uh...

32:47.550 --> 32:51.054
...an occasional, unh, dent.

32:51.804 --> 32:53.056
<i>Proposition:</i>

32:53.348 --> 32:55.350
<i>Right or wrong...</i>

32:55.558 --> 32:59.062
<i>...they have the might.
So right or wrong, they're always right.</i>

32:59.228 --> 33:01.522
<i>That's wrong.
Right?</i>

33:02.273 --> 33:03.900
Jenny.

33:05.443 --> 33:07.278
Jenny.

33:10.365 --> 33:12.241
Jenny.

33:15.578 --> 33:17.080
- Jenny.
- I'm here.

33:19.749 --> 33:21.376
Jenny, Jenny.

33:21.542 --> 33:24.337
Suppose we create
a new order of chivalry?

33:25.630 --> 33:28.925
A new order where
might is only used for right.

33:29.425 --> 33:32.595
To improve instead of to destroy.
Look, we'll invite all knights...

33:32.804 --> 33:36.557
...and kings of all kingdoms to lay down
their arms to come and join us.

33:36.891 --> 33:38.059
Oh, yes, Jenny.

33:38.518 --> 33:39.769
And we'll...

33:40.311 --> 33:43.064
...take one of the large rooms
in the castle...

33:43.272 --> 33:46.359
...put a table in it
and all the knights will gather at it.

33:46.693 --> 33:47.860
And do what?

33:48.986 --> 33:50.488
Talk across it.

33:51.447 --> 33:52.740
Debate.

33:53.116 --> 33:55.284
Make laws.
Plan improvements.

33:56.244 --> 34:00.123
But, Arthur, do you think
all the knights will ever want to...

34:00.415 --> 34:03.334
...to do such a ridiculously
peaceful thing?

34:03.918 --> 34:06.713
We'll make it a great honor.

34:07.296 --> 34:09.966
Very fashionable.
Everyone will want to join.

34:10.425 --> 34:11.634
Only now...

34:13.052 --> 34:15.554
...the knights will whack only for good.

34:15.763 --> 34:17.098
Might for right.

34:21.101 --> 34:22.937
Might for right.

34:26.315 --> 34:27.400
Might...

34:27.608 --> 34:29.402
...for right!

34:30.277 --> 34:31.320
That's it, Jenny!

34:33.781 --> 34:35.116
Might....

34:36.617 --> 34:39.161
No, not might is right!

34:40.455 --> 34:41.998
Might...

34:42.623 --> 34:43.791
...for...

34:44.876 --> 34:45.918
...right!

34:47.628 --> 34:49.213
It's very original. Heh.

34:49.380 --> 34:50.965
Yes. Yes, yes. And--

34:51.132 --> 34:52.382
And civilized, Jenny.

34:52.592 --> 34:54.927
It will have to be
an awfully large table.

34:55.136 --> 34:59.599
What of jealousy? All will claim
superiority and want to sit at the head.

35:00.308 --> 35:01.684
We'll make it...

35:02.101 --> 35:04.103
...a round table.

35:04.312 --> 35:06.230
So there is no head.

35:06.647 --> 35:09.108
A round table!

35:09.734 --> 35:15.698
Round...

35:18.075 --> 35:20.495
...table.

35:20.661 --> 35:24.832
My father's got one
that would be perfect. It seats 150.

35:25.041 --> 35:28.377
He had it as a wedding present
and he never used it.

35:29.504 --> 35:31.631
<i>We'll send the heralds</i>

35:31.798 --> 35:33.841
<i>Riding through the country</i>

35:35.343 --> 35:39.514
<i>Tell every living person far and near</i>

35:41.015 --> 35:43.184
<i>That there is simply not</i>

35:43.518 --> 35:46.187
<i>In all the world a spot</i>

35:46.854 --> 35:51.526
<i>Where rules a more resplendent king</i>

35:53.194 --> 35:55.112
<i>Than here</i>

35:56.739 --> 35:58.866
<i>In Camelot</i>

37:55.608 --> 37:58.736
<i>Camelot</i>

37:59.737 --> 38:02.073
<i>Camelot</i>

38:02.281 --> 38:07.536
<i>In far off France
I hear you call</i>

38:08.329 --> 38:11.374
<i>Camelot</i>

38:11.874 --> 38:14.001
<i>Camelot</i>

38:14.585 --> 38:20.132
<i>To you alone I'll give my all</i>

38:20.299 --> 38:24.470
<i>I know in my soul
What you expect of me</i>

38:24.971 --> 38:28.641
<i>And all that and more I shall be</i>

38:29.976 --> 38:33.980
<i>A knight of the table round
Should be invincible</i>

38:34.939 --> 38:38.359
<i>Succeed where a less fantastic man
Would fail</i>

38:39.151 --> 38:43.489
<i>Climb a wall no one else can climb
Cleave a dragon in record time</i>

38:43.823 --> 38:47.827
<i>Swim a moat
In a coat of heavy iron mail</i>

38:48.995 --> 38:52.999
<i>No matter the pain
He ought to be unwinceable</i>

38:53.833 --> 38:57.837
<i>Impossible deeds
Should be his daily fare</i>

38:58.504 --> 39:00.673
<i>But where in the world</i>

39:01.007 --> 39:03.676
<i>Is there in the world</i>

39:04.010 --> 39:11.559
<i>A man so extraordinaire?</i>

39:14.186 --> 39:17.690
C'est moi, c'est moi
<i>I'm forced to admit</i>

39:18.024 --> 39:21.360
<i>'Tis I I humbly reply</i>

39:21.569 --> 39:24.864
<i>That mortal who these marvels can do</i>

39:25.197 --> 39:28.325
C'est moi, c'est moi <i>'Tis I</i>

39:28.951 --> 39:32.580
<i>I've never lost
In battle or game</i>

39:32.788 --> 39:36.000
<i>I'm simply the best by far</i>

39:36.375 --> 39:40.129
<i>When swords are crossed
'Tis always the same</i>

39:40.463 --> 39:43.799
<i>One blow and</i> Au revoir

39:44.216 --> 39:47.970
C'est moi, c'est moi
<i>So admirably fit</i>

39:48.220 --> 39:51.974
<i>A French Prometheus Unbound</i>

39:52.308 --> 39:56.312
<i>And here am I With valor untold</i>

39:56.979 --> 39:59.648
<i>Exceptionally brave</i>

39:59.982 --> 40:03.152
<i>Amazingly bold</i>

40:03.611 --> 40:06.989
<i>To serve at the table round</i>

40:07.782 --> 40:11.452
<i>The soul of a knight
Should be a thing remarkable</i>

40:12.161 --> 40:15.664
<i>His heart and his mind
As pure as morning dew</i>

40:16.457 --> 40:20.795
<i>With a will and a self-restraint
That's the envy of every saint</i>

40:21.128 --> 40:24.632
<i>He could easily work a miracle or two</i>

40:26.342 --> 40:30.221
<i>To love and desire
He ought to be unsparkable</i>

40:30.971 --> 40:35.142
<i>The ways of the flesh
Should offer no allure</i>

40:35.476 --> 40:40.147
<i>But where in the world
Is there in the world</i>

40:40.648 --> 40:43.484
<i>A man so untouched</i>

40:43.818 --> 40:49.907
<i>And pure?</i>

40:50.825 --> 40:51.867
C'est moi

40:52.701 --> 40:56.163
C'est moi, c'est moi
<i>I blush to disclose</i>

40:56.497 --> 41:00.000
<i>I'm far too noble to lie</i>

41:00.334 --> 41:04.255
<i>That man in whom
These qualities bloom</i>

41:04.463 --> 41:08.008
C'est moi, C'est moi <i>'Tis I</i>

41:08.425 --> 41:12.304
<i>I've never strayed
From all I believe</i>

41:12.513 --> 41:15.850
<i>I'm blessed with an iron will</i>

41:16.183 --> 41:20.062
<i>Had I been made
The partner of Eve</i>

41:20.229 --> 41:23.691
<i>We'd be in Eden still</i>

41:24.275 --> 41:28.195
C'est moi, c'est moi
<i>The angels have chosen</i>

41:28.404 --> 41:32.032
<i>To fight their battles below</i>

41:32.575 --> 41:37.371
<i>And here am I
As pure as a prayer</i>

41:38.205 --> 41:40.666
<i>Incredibly clean</i>

41:41.417 --> 41:44.086
<i>With virtue to spare</i>

41:44.753 --> 41:48.757
<i>The godliest man I know</i>
C'est moi!

42:18.829 --> 42:20.873
Oh, King Arthur!

42:21.081 --> 42:23.834
What caliber of man you must be...

42:24.335 --> 42:27.421
...to have envisioned
a new order of life.

42:28.130 --> 42:30.758
I worship you before knowing you.

42:56.575 --> 42:58.244
Don't run away, coward!

42:58.869 --> 43:00.663
Come back and fight!

43:32.528 --> 43:33.696
The swine!

43:33.904 --> 43:36.156
- Are you hurt, Your Majesty?
- Fine.

43:41.412 --> 43:42.705
Please!

43:46.709 --> 43:48.585
The next time you traffic with me...

43:48.836 --> 43:52.798
...remember, you challenge
the right arm of King Arthur.

43:53.882 --> 43:55.175
Really?

43:57.636 --> 43:59.430
I am King Arthur.

44:04.893 --> 44:06.395
What?

44:08.314 --> 44:09.523
You...

44:11.317 --> 44:12.860
...are the king!

44:13.068 --> 44:16.280
Yes, almost the late king.

44:17.239 --> 44:19.742
And I struck you?

44:25.247 --> 44:26.665
Your Majesty!

44:27.916 --> 44:28.959
Your Majesty.

44:29.126 --> 44:30.627
I'm Lancelot Du Lac.

44:30.836 --> 44:34.089
In France I heard of your new order
and came to join.

44:34.423 --> 44:36.467
I beg Your Majesty to forgive me.

44:37.426 --> 44:39.094
Not because I deserve it...

44:39.261 --> 44:41.680
...but because by forgiving me...

44:41.889 --> 44:43.182
...I'll suffer more.

44:43.474 --> 44:45.100
But, really, dear chap...

44:45.309 --> 44:47.895
...I don't want you to suffer at all.

44:48.062 --> 44:52.024
I want to congratulate you.
Please rise. You, too, squire.

44:52.191 --> 44:53.984
Uh, I can't, <i>Mon roi.</i>

44:54.193 --> 44:58.072
- I'm too ashamed to lift my head.
- Well, then I command you.

44:58.614 --> 45:01.325
I have never felt
a bash in my chest quite like it.

45:01.533 --> 45:04.286
It was most spectacular.
Where did you learn to do it?

45:05.287 --> 45:08.040
My skill comes from training, <i>Mon roi.</i>

45:08.916 --> 45:11.168
My strength from purity.

45:13.545 --> 45:16.382
Well, that's a unique recipe.

45:16.673 --> 45:19.176
He's a unique man, Your Majesty.

45:19.385 --> 45:23.305
At the age of fourteen
he could defeat any jouster in France.

45:23.722 --> 45:26.475
His father, King Ban,
made me his squire.

45:26.683 --> 45:28.227
- King Ban?
- Yes.

45:29.144 --> 45:30.646
In France?

45:31.814 --> 45:33.482
What did you say your name was?

45:33.732 --> 45:36.318
Lancelot Du Lac, Your Majesty.

45:37.986 --> 45:41.824
You're Lancelot?
I was told you were coming.

45:42.741 --> 45:45.160
You were told?

45:46.078 --> 45:47.496
Yes.

45:47.663 --> 45:50.374
By Merlyn, the court magician.

45:50.582 --> 45:51.959
He said to me one day:

45:52.126 --> 45:57.381
"Arthur, keep your eye out for a
Frenchman called Lancelot Du Lac.

45:57.589 --> 46:01.051
He will come to the court of Camelot
and he will be...."

46:02.594 --> 46:04.179
What was it now?

46:04.513 --> 46:05.639
"He will be...."

46:06.348 --> 46:09.059
Your ally, if you'll take me.

46:09.268 --> 46:11.728
Your friend, who asks no friendship.

46:11.937 --> 46:14.189
Your defender when you need one...

46:14.398 --> 46:16.900
...whose body is your sword to brandish.

46:17.609 --> 46:19.611
Did he prophesy that, Your Majesty?

46:19.820 --> 46:22.364
For all that, I am.

46:23.115 --> 46:24.741
Really, my dear fellow...

46:24.950 --> 46:27.703
...this is far more
than I could wish for...

46:28.370 --> 46:30.539
...uh, or even ask.

46:31.415 --> 46:33.250
Then you will accept me?

46:33.459 --> 46:35.586
Without hesitation.

46:35.836 --> 46:38.714
- We will arrange for your knighthood.
- Oh, thank you!

46:43.469 --> 46:46.388
We must arrange for
your knighthood immediately.

46:46.597 --> 46:49.641
Oh, no. No, Your Majesty.
All you know of me is words.

46:49.850 --> 46:52.561
Invest me because of deeds, sire.
Give me an order.

46:52.769 --> 46:54.062
- Now?
- This moment.

46:54.271 --> 46:57.399
Send me on a mission.
Is there some wrong I can right?

46:57.608 --> 47:00.819
Some enemy I can battle?
Some peril I can undertake?

47:01.653 --> 47:04.907
Well, actually,
there's not much going on today.

47:05.491 --> 47:09.369
Uh, it's the first of May. The Queen and
some of the court have gone a-Maying.

47:09.953 --> 47:12.164
Gone a-Maying?

47:12.581 --> 47:14.875
Yes, it's a sort of...

47:16.502 --> 47:17.961
...picnic?

47:18.337 --> 47:21.423
They eat berries
and chase young girls around--

47:21.590 --> 47:23.258
Picnic?

47:23.425 --> 47:26.261
It's a custom we have here.

47:26.470 --> 47:28.931
This is England, you know.

47:29.097 --> 47:31.767
And this is the season
for gathering flowers.

47:32.100 --> 47:34.269
Knights gathering flowers?

47:34.436 --> 47:36.772
Well, someone has to do it!

47:38.482 --> 47:40.776
And besides, it's....

47:41.610 --> 47:43.779
It's civilized.

47:44.029 --> 47:46.865
And civilization should have...

47:47.074 --> 47:50.077
...a few gentle hobbies.

47:52.246 --> 47:53.288
Come, come.

47:54.706 --> 47:56.959
I want you to meet the queen.

47:59.419 --> 48:02.339
Dap, take the horses and feed them.

48:12.641 --> 48:15.686
By George, Lancelot!

48:15.852 --> 48:18.480
I suddenly remembered
what Merlyn said of you.

48:18.939 --> 48:20.607
How strange!

48:21.149 --> 48:25.279
He said that you would be the
greatest knight ever to sit at my table.

48:25.779 --> 48:28.031
That was long before
I thought of a table.

48:28.240 --> 48:30.826
So he knew it would exist.

48:31.368 --> 48:35.330
I.... I.... Oh, dear!
I thought he meant a dining table.

48:35.497 --> 48:37.124
But he meant this.

48:37.332 --> 48:38.792
The Round Table!

48:39.001 --> 48:42.004
And I have stumbled on my future.

48:42.170 --> 48:43.589
I've done...

48:43.797 --> 48:45.465
...the right thing.

48:45.841 --> 48:48.427
Did you ever doubt it, Your Majesty?

48:48.677 --> 48:51.013
Oh, of course, of course.

48:51.179 --> 48:52.681
Only fools...

48:52.889 --> 48:54.433
...never doubt.

48:55.434 --> 48:57.686
